This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Attorney Andrew I. Martinez in court.  Sue Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty Martinez notes a family member of the DE told him DE has been deported back to Mexico.  Objects to forfeiture of cash bond.  State requests bond be forfeited.  Atty Martinez states sister posted cash.  Court orders bond returned to the person who posted it.

Attorney Andrew I. Martinez in court.  Sue Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty. Martinez states DE has been deported since Jan. 8th.  State requests warrant.  Atty. Martinez objects.    Based on non-appearance, court authorized warrant.  Begin bond forfeiture.

records.addlTxt:
Pre-trial conference at 01-15-2016 10:00 am.
Return date at 01-26-2016 01:00 pm.

Defendant Alejandro Ulrico Ortega Vidal appears by video from the jail w/interpreter Yvon R.  Court states case and appearances.  Court finds DE conditionally indigent and appoints Atty Andrew Martinez (144 4th Ave #2, Baraboo (608) 355-2000).  To reimburse COC's office $100/month beginning 1/15/2016 and then the fifteenth of each month thereafter.

Pre-trial conference at 12-11-2015 10:00 am.
Return date at 12-22-2015 01:00 pm.

Defendant Alejandro Ulrico Ortega Vidal appeared by video means with Attorney Raabe and interpreter Alejandra K. Prosecuting Atty Sue Mueller appeared for State of Wisconsin.  Defendant waives reading of complaint.   Advised rights to an attorney.  State request cash bond.  State goes through criminal history.  File set for pre-trial conference/return date. $500.00 CASH bond set.  Special bond conditions as follows:  No contact with E.O., her chidlren, residence or her employment.  No following or stalking the victim.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for December 11, 2015 at 10:00 am.  Return date scheduled for December 22, 2015 at 01:00 pm.
